{"version":1,"ops":[{"author":{"id":"9eb510892d1accc0c715d21128d216b2e6f74967"},"files":null,"message":"There is some kind of data/event race combined with the input-update-synch loop\nin tui or the terminal emulator wherein an update might not get synched\nproperly, leaving the visible UI 'one frame behind'.\n\nReproduce:\nThis is far from 100% reproducible, but to increase the odds:\n1. disable cursor blink rate entirely (prevent timer event loop),\n2. create a full-screen terminal, use ttf fonts at a small size\n   (increases render times)\n3. look at text with partial updates that take emojii (render-jitter/cache)\n\nBest way forward is probably to grab a snapshot of both the shmif- segments\nand the tsm/tui state machines, check event-queue load, vready flag state and\ndrawing state.\n\nBest solution still would be the planned renderer refactor to inch towards\nserver side rendering which would vastly simplify everything tui.","timestamp":1559485574,"title":"(tui/term) dirty/tracking refreshing problems","type":1}]}